Since then, other coins like Shiba Inu, Pepe, have followed, showing that even coins with no deep utility can still move markets.

Then in 2013 the @dogecoin was created by Billy Markus and Jackson Palmer as a joke currency.

It was originally created as a fork on @litecoin and it later developed it's own blockchain using a proof of work(PoW) consensus mechanism and a scrypt hashing algorithm.

The @dogecoin was simply created out of a meme.

A Japanese lady had posted photos of her dog: Kabosu on social media which is a shiba inu (dog breed). 

A lot of people found one particular picture really cute, it went viral and became the face of the doge meme. https://t.co/zuPzlTUaPd
